ProposalInformation.Title: OTE-13 NIRCam-Only Coarse MIMF
ProposalInformation.Abstract: Measure and correct NIRCam field dependent PSF differences using SM tilt and de-center moves, along with compensating move of the primary using the PMSAs. Note this is different from “NIRCam Multi-Field” in that the data is taken not with the weak lenses, but with the segment image array acting as a Shack-Hartmann wavefront sensor. This is done via 31 observations. Observations 1-16 take data for the first Coarse MIMF sensing, with Obs 1-4 setting up the regular medium array, 5-9 taking the MIMF data, 10-11 setting up the inverted array, and 12-16 taking the MIMF data. The WFSC scientist will analyze the data from 5-9 and 12-16 to determine the correction that is applied via Obs 17. After the correction, Observations 18 to 31 may be executed to make another duplicate round of MIMF observations and confirm the correction was successful.
ProposalInformation.ObservingDescription:
-------------------- Purpose: -------------------- Measure and correct NIRCam field dependent PSF differences using SM tilt and de-center moves, along with compensating move of the primary using the PMSAs. Note this is different from “NIRCam Multi-Field” in that the data is taken not with the weak lenses, but with the segment image array acting as a Shack-Hartmann wavefront sensor.
-------------------- Rationale: --------------------
-------------------- Description: -------------------- There will be 31 observations. Observations 1-16 take data for the first Coarse MIMF sensing: Observations 1-4 set up the regular medium array; 5-9 take data. 10-11 set up the inverted array, 12-16 take data. The WFSC scientist will analyze the data from 5-9 and 12-16 to determine the correction.
If a correction is needed, Observation 17 applies that correction to the SM and PM. Then after a correction, Observations 18 to 31 are copies of 3 to 16, to take a second set of Coarse MIMF data to confirm the correction was successful. Obs 18-19 set up the regular medium array, 20-24 take data, 25-26 set up the inverted array, 27-31 take data. The WFSC scientist will analyze the data from 20-24 and 27-31 to confirm the correction or determine if another iteration is required.
There is some small chance an additional correction might be needed; in that contingency make additional copies of 17 to 31 to perform that correction and then confirm.
The first two observations use coarse PCS mode. All other observations use tracking via segment guiding. All observations are linked with the same V3 PA.
-------------------- Notes / Open Questions: -------------------- - Multiple GS IDs are needed for this program based on the pointing of each observation. E.g., FP1 - FP5 MIMF observations each need their own GS ID. List of GS ID candidates for each observation will be generated by VSS and the proposal will need to be updated.
